description:
The consumer-spi was using a plugin key of `${atlassian.plugin.key}` - the value was not being substituted because... I deleted that property from the pom (facepalm).

It was working in refapp and JIRA BTF as there are no other plugins with that key. However when it tries to load in JIRA OD or Connie it looks like a duplicate of another plugin with that key.

Also, cleaned up the imports while I was in there.
title: OAUTH-332 - give the consumer-spi a proper plugin key

summary.raw:
The consumer-spi was using a plugin key of `${atlassian.plugin.key}` - the value was not being substituted because... I deleted that property from the pom (facepalm).

It was working in refapp and JIRA BTF as there are no other plugins with that key. However when it tries to load in JIRA OD or Connie it looks like a duplicate of another plugin with that key.

Also, cleaned up the imports while I was in there.
summary.html:
The consumer-spi was using a plugin key of ${atlassian.plugin.key} - the value was not being substituted because... I deleted that property from the pom (facepalm).

It was working in refapp and JIRA BTF as there are no other plugins with that key. However when it tries to load in JIRA OD or Connie it looks like a duplicate of another plugin with that key.

Also, cleaned up the imports while I was in there.
